# Basic Python Function and Conditional

## Description
This script defines a simple function to add two numbers and checks whether the result is even or odd. It serves as a beginner-friendly example of how functions and conditional statements work in Python.

## Features
- Define and call functions
- Use if-else statements
- Demonstrate modular code and logical thinking

## Requirements
- Python 3.x

## How to Run
```bash
python function_updated.py
